cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for generating paraphrastic sentence embeddings. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses neural machine translation, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves techniques for data filtering and scaling up to generate large training sets, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions exploring differences in output between neural machine translation and human-written sentences, which could potentially fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision) if the differences are visual in nature.
